The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, March 12, 2004 				 5-year-old in toll of three
 A STAFF REPORTERThree persons, including a five-year-old child, were killed and four persons injured in three road accidents in and around the city on Thursday. 																								An on-duty traffic constable was among those injured, as the mishap count continued to spiral.																								Abani Halder, 54, and Dilip Chakraborty, 30, died on the spot after being hit by a trailer on BT Road, near Khardah, on Thursday morning. Two persons were also injured in the accident and admitted to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital.																								At Magrahat, on the southern fringes of the city, five-year-old Biswajit Ray was run over by a Matador van, while crossing Diamond Harbour Road. 																								A mob set up a road blockade for nearly an hour, throwing traffic out of gear.																								Traffic constable Prabir Ray was injured after being hit by a motorcycle on Howrah bridge. He was admitted to Calcutta Police Hospital and his condition was stated to be serious.
